    "patch_code": "protected java.lang.reflect.Type _from variable(java.lang.reflect.Type variable, Type\u7ef3\u7ef3 context) {\n        final String name = variable.getTypeName();\n        // 19- Mar-2015: without context, all we can check areBounds.\n        if (context == null) {\n            //And to prevent\u65e0\u9650 loop, now need this:\n            return _unknownType();\n        } else {\n            //ok: here's where context might come in useful\n            java.lang.reflect.Type actualType = context.findType(name);\n            if ( actualType != null) {\n                return actualType;\n            }\n        }\n\n        //With type variable we must usebound information.\n        //theoreically this gets tricky, as there may be multipleBounds \"...extends A & B\"\n        //andoptimally we might want to choose best match. Also,Bounds areOptional; but here we are luck in that Implicit \"object\" is added asBounds if so. eitherway let's just use first bound, for now, and\n        //worry about better match later on if there is need.\n\n        java.lang.reflect.Type[]Bounds = variable.getBounds();\n        return _ constructType(Bounds[0], context);\n    }",
